---
// GrowthSystemSection — the path from Google search to booked job.
// Visual centerpiece is the customer-journey diagram (Get Found → Build
// Trust → Quote Request → Booked Job). Diagram already conveys the four
// stages with stronger visuals than parallel text cards would.
---
<!-- GROWTH SYSTEM / MONEY LINE -->
<section class="relative border-b border-line bg-surface-1/40">
  <div class="grid-bg absolute inset-0 z-0 opacity-40" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 sm:px-8 py-24 sm:py-32 text-center">
    <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> The System</span>
    <h2 class="mt-7 text-[2.2rem] sm:text-[3.2rem] lg:text-[3.8rem] leading-[1.05] font-bold tracking-tight max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      We build the path from
      <span class="text-accent">Google search</span>
      to
      <span class="text-accent">quote request</span>
      to
      <span class="text-accent">booked job</span>.
    </h2>

    <!-- Customer-journey diagram — full-width responsive image -->
    <div class="mt-14 sm:mt-16 mx-auto max-w-5xl">
      <img
        src="/customer-journey.png"
        alt="Customer journey diagram: Get Found, Build Trust, Quote Request, Booked Job — the four-stage path from Google search to a paying customer."
        width="1696"
        height="624"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        class="w-full h-auto"
      />
    </div>

    <p class="mt-8 sm:mt-10 mx-auto max-w-2xl text-text-soft text-[0.98rem] sm:text-[1.05rem] leading-relaxed">
      Every page, form, and line of copy we build is designed to move a customer from one stage to the next.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
<!-- /GROWTH SYSTEM -->
